.	O

.	O

020	O

.	O

Pigments	O

appliqués	O

combat	O

Disappointments	O
are	O
inevitable	O
,	O
and	O
how	O
we	O
cope	O
with	O
them	O
is	O
often	O
a	O
defining	O
moment	O
in	O
our	O
lives	O
.	O
How	O
we	O
respond	O
to	O
disappointment	O
is	O
often	O
influenced	O
by	O
our	O
upbringing	O
;	O
some	O
people	O
seek	O
to	O
avoid	O
disappointment	O
by	O
underachieving	O
(	O
setting	O
their	O
expectations	O
permanently	O
low	O
)	O
while	O
others	O
seek	O
to	O
avoid	O
it	O
by	O
overachieving	O
(	O
setting	O
their	O
expectations	O
unattainably	O
high	O
)	O
.	O
Regardless	O
of	O
which	O
way	O
we	O
lean	O
,	O
we	O
can	O
learn	O
to	O
respond	O
healthily	O
to	O
disappointment	O
by	O
adopting	O
a	O
coping	O
style	O
that	O
seeks	O
to	O
understand	O
what	O
happened	O
,	O
checks	O
whether	O
our	O
expectations	O
were	O
reasonable	O
,	O
reevaluates	O
our	O
perceptions	O
and	O
behaviors	O
,	O
and	O
seeks	O
positive	O
solutions	O
instead	O
of	O
dwelling	O
on	O
the	O
past	O
.	O
Introspection	O
can	O
be	O
helpful	O
,	O
but	O
rumination	O
is	O
often	O
not	O
.	O

disappointment	O
is	O
inevitable	O
,	O
being	O

is	O
always	O
a	O
choice	O

Switching	O
